    • Class it.polimi.ingsw.model.SlimGameModel

      class SlimGameModel extends Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • availableSlots
          Map<PlayerToken,List<Coords>> availableSlots
          Tracks coordinates of slots on which cards can be played for each player. Coordinates do not depend on the card.
        • cardsPlayability
          Map<PlayerToken,Map<Integer,List<Pair<CardSide,Boolean>>>> cardsPlayability
          Map that track whether a card can be placed or not, both sides considered for each player.
        • commonObjectives
          List<Integer> commonObjectives
          List containing the ids of the common objectives.
        • goldDeck
          List<Integer> goldDeck
          The gold deck as a list of ids, where the first one belongs to the card at the bottom of the deck.
        • resourceDeck
          List<Integer> resourceDeck
          The resource deck as a list of ids, where the first one belongs to the card at the bottom of the deck.
        • scores
          Map<PlayerToken,Integer> scores
          Map to keep track of the scoreboard.
        • tokenToElements
          Map<PlayerToken,Map<Elements,Integer>> tokenToElements
          Map that keeps track of elements for every player.
        • tokenToHand
          Map<PlayerToken,List<Integer>> tokenToHand
          Map to keep track of each player's hand.
        • tokenToPlayedCards
          Map<PlayerToken,Map<Integer,Trio<Integer,CardSide,Coords>>> tokenToPlayedCards
          Map to keep track of the cards placement order, for every player.
        • tokenToSecretObjective
          Map<PlayerToken,Integer> tokenToSecretObjective
          Map that keeps the id of the private objective of a player, for every player.
        • visibleGoldCardsList
          List<Integer> visibleGoldCardsList
          Structure to keep track of the ids of the cards in the visible gold card list.
        • visibleResourceCardsList
          List<Integer> visibleResourceCardsList
          Structure to keep track of the ids of the cards in the visible resource card list.
